#: dictee-setup.py:4886
msgid "Enable post-processing (regex rules + dictionary)"
msgstr "Activer le post-traitement (règles regex + dictionnaire)"

#: dictee-setup.py:4900
msgid "Number conversion (text2num)"
msgstr "Conversion des nombres (text2num)"

#: dictee-setup.py:4903
msgid ""
"Converts spoken numbers to digits.\n"
"Example: \"vingt-trois\" → \"23\""
msgstr ""
"Convertit les nombres parlés en chiffres.\n"
"Exemple : \"vingt-trois\" → \"23\""

#: dictee-setup.py:4906
msgid "Auto-capitalization"
msgstr "Capitalisation automatique"

#: dictee-setup.py:4909
msgid ""
"Capitalizes the first letter after sentence-ending\n"
"punctuation (. ! ?). Parakeet does this natively,\n"
"but post-processing rules may alter the text —\n"
"this ensures correct capitalization afterwards.\n"
"Essential for Vosk/Whisper backends."
msgstr ""
"Met en majuscule la première lettre après une ponctuation\n"
"de fin de phrase (. ! ?). Parakeet le fait nativement,\n"
"mais les règles de post-traitement peuvent modifier le texte —\n"
"ceci garantit une capitalisation correcte ensuite.\n"
"Indispensable pour les backends Vosk/Whisper."

#: dictee-setup.py:4915 dictee-setup.py:4966
msgid "Regex rules"
msgstr "Règles regex"

#: dictee-setup.py:4918
msgid ""
"Applies regex substitution rules to fix\n"
"common ASR errors (voice commands,\n"
"punctuation, formatting)."
msgstr ""
"Applique des règles de substitution regex pour corriger\n"
"les erreurs ASR courantes (commandes vocales,\n"
"ponctuation, mise en forme)."

#: dictee-setup.py:4922 dictee-setup.py:4959 dictee-setup.py:9325
msgid "Dictionary"
msgstr "Dictionnaire"

#: dictee-setup.py:4925
msgid ""
"Replaces words using the dictionary.\n"
"Exact matching on word boundaries."
msgstr ""
"Remplace les mots à l'aide du dictionnaire.\n"
"Correspondance exacte sur les limites de mots."

#: dictee-setup.py:4928 dictee-setup.py:4973 dictee-setup.py:9269
msgid "Continuation"
msgstr "Continuation"

#: dictee-setup.py:4931
msgid ""
"Removes erroneous periods after continuation words\n"
"(articles, prepositions, conjunctions, pronouns, verbs)\n"
"to keep sentences flowing naturally across push-to-talk segments.\n"
"\n"
"Voice command: say your continuation keyword at the start\n"
"of a push to remove the previous punctuation and continue\n"
"in lowercase. The keyword is configurable per language\n"
"in the Continuation tab."
msgstr ""
"Supprime les points erronés après les mots de continuation\n"
"(articles, prépositions, conjonctions, pronoms, verbes)\n"
"pour garder les phrases fluides entre les segments push-to-talk.\n"
"\n"
"Commande vocale : dites votre mot-clé de continuation au début\n"
"d'un push pour supprimer la ponctuation précédente et continuer\n"
"en minuscule. Le mot-clé est configurable par langue\n"
"dans l'onglet Continuation."

#: dictee-setup.py:4980
msgid "Language rules"
msgstr "Règles de langue"

#: dictee-setup.py:4991
msgid "Edit mode"
msgstr "Mode édition"

#: dictee-setup.py:5023
msgid "LLM grammar correction (ollama)"
msgstr "Correction grammaticale LLM (ollama)"

#: dictee-setup.py:5056
msgid "Force CPU (free GPU VRAM)"
msgstr "Forcer le CPU (libérer la VRAM GPU)"

#: dictee-setup.py:5061
msgid "~2 GB VRAM with Ministral 3B (+ ~2.5 GB Parakeet)"
msgstr "~2 Go VRAM avec Ministral 3B (+ ~2,5 Go Parakeet)"

#: dictee-setup.py:5254
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Language-specific rules (elisions, contractions, typography) applied to the "
"source language only. Currently: <b>{lang}</b>. Only the rules matching your "
"source language will be active."
msgstr ""
"Règles spécifiques à la langue (élisions, contractions, typographie) "
"appliquées à la langue source uniquement. Actuellement : <b>{lang}</b>. "
"Seules les règles correspondant à votre langue source seront actives."

#: dictee-setup.py:5266
msgid "Elisions"
msgstr "Élisions"

#: dictee-setup.py:5269
msgid ""
"Applies French elision rules.\n"
"Example: \"le arbre\" → \"l'arbre\",\n"
"\"de eau\" → \"d'eau\""
msgstr ""
"Applique les règles d'élision françaises.\n"
"Exemple : \"le arbre\" → \"l'arbre\",\n"
"\"de eau\" → \"d'eau\""

#: dictee-setup.py:5273
msgid "Typography (non-breaking spaces)"
msgstr "Typographie (espaces insécables)"

#: dictee-setup.py:5276
msgid ""
"Inserts non-breaking spaces before French\n"
"punctuation marks (: ; ! ? « »)\n"
"as required by French typography rules."
msgstr ""
"Insère des espaces insécables avant les signes\n"
"de ponctuation français (: ; ! ? « »)\n"
"conformément aux règles typographiques françaises."

#: dictee-setup.py:5286
msgid ""
"No specific rules needed. Contractions (don't, I'm, can't) are handled "
"natively by the ASR engine."
msgstr ""
"Aucune règle spécifique nécessaire. Les contractions (don't, I'm, can't) "
"sont gérées nativement par le moteur ASR."

#: dictee-setup.py:5297
msgid "Elisions & contractions"
msgstr "Élisions et contractions"

#: dictee-setup.py:5300
msgid ""
"Italian elisions and prepositional contractions.\n"
"Elisions: \"lo uomo\" → \"l'uomo\", \"di accordo\" → \"d'accordo\"\n"
"Contractions: \"di il\" → \"del\", \"a la\" → \"alla\",\n"
"\"in il\" → \"nel\", \"su la\" → \"sulla\""
msgstr ""
"Élisions et contractions prépositionnelles italiennes.\n"
"Élisions : \"lo uomo\" → \"l'uomo\", \"di accordo\" → \"d'accordo\"\n"
"Contractions : \"di il\" → \"del\", \"a la\" → \"alla\",\n"
"\"in il\" → \"nel\", \"su la\" → \"sulla\""

#: dictee-setup.py:5312
msgid "Contractions & inverted punctuation"
msgstr "Contractions et ponctuation inversée"

#: dictee-setup.py:5315
msgid ""
"Spanish contractions and inverted punctuation.\n"
"Contractions: \"a el\" → \"al\", \"de el\" → \"del\"\n"
"Punctuation: adds ¿ before questions and ¡ before exclamations."
msgstr ""
"Contractions et ponctuation inversée espagnoles.\n"
"Contractions : \"a el\" → \"al\", \"de el\" → \"del\"\n"
"Ponctuation : ajoute ¿ avant les questions et ¡ avant les exclamations."

#: dictee-setup.py:5326 dictee-setup.py:5355
msgid "Contractions"
msgstr "Contractions"

#: dictee-setup.py:5329
msgid ""
"Portuguese fused contractions.\n"
"\"de o\" → \"do\", \"em a\" → \"na\", \"por os\" → \"pelos\",\n"
"\"de este\" → \"deste\", \"em ele\" → \"nele\""
msgstr ""
"Contractions fusionnées portugaises.\n"
"\"de o\" → \"do\", \"em a\" → \"na\", \"por os\" → \"pelos\",\n"
"\"de este\" → \"deste\", \"em ele\" → \"nele\""

#: dictee-setup.py:5340 dictee-setup.py:5369
msgid "Contractions & typography"
msgstr "Contractions et typographie"

#: dictee-setup.py:5343
msgid ""
"German contractions and typography.\n"
"Contractions: \"an dem\" → \"am\", \"in dem\" → \"im\",\n"
"\"zu dem\" → \"zum\", \"zu der\" → \"zur\"\n"
"Typography: \"text\" → \\u201etext\\u201c (German quotes)"
msgstr ""
"Contractions et typographie allemandes.\n"
"Contractions : \"an dem\" → \"am\", \"in dem\" → \"im\",\n"
"\"zu dem\" → \"zum\", \"zu der\" → \"zur\"\n"
"Typographie : \"text\" → \\u201etext\\u201c (guillemets allemands)"

#: dictee-setup.py:5358
msgid ""
"Dutch contractions and time expressions.\n"
"\"het\" → \"'t\", \"een\" → \"'n\"\n"
"\"in de morgens\" → \"'s morgens\""
msgstr ""
"Contractions et expressions temporelles néerlandaises.\n"
"\"het\" → \"'t\", \"een\" → \"'n\"\n"
"\"in de morgens\" → \"'s morgens\""

#: dictee-setup.py:5372
msgid ""
"Romanian contractions and typography.\n"
"\"nu am\" → \"n-am\", \"într o\" → \"într-o\"\n"
"Typography: \"text\" → \\u201etext\\u201c (Romanian quotes)"
msgstr ""
"Contractions et typographie roumaines.\n"
"\"nu am\" → \"n-am\", \"într o\" → \"într-o\"\n"
"Typographie : \"text\" → \\u201etext\\u201c (guillemets roumains)"

#: dictee-setup.py:5391
msgid "Command suffix:"
msgstr "Suffixe de commande :"

#: dictee-setup.py:5393
msgid ""
"<b>Command suffix</b><br><br>Some voice commands use words that also exist "
"as normal words. The suffix is a word you say <b>after</b> the ambiguous "
"command to confirm it's a voice command, not a regular word."
"<br><br><b>Examples by language:</b><br>• FR (suffix = \"suivi\"): \"point "
"suivi\" → \".\" — but \"un bon point\" → kept as text<br>• EN (suffix = "
"\"done\"): \"period done\" → \".\" — but \"a long period\" → kept as "
"text<br>• DE (suffix = \"weiter\"): \"Punkt weiter\" → \".\" — but \"ein "
"guter Punkt\" → kept as text<br>• ES (suffix = \"listo\"): \"punto listo\" → "
"\".\" — but \"un buen punto\" → kept as text<br>• IT (suffix = \"seguito\"): "
"\"punto seguito\" → \".\" — but \"un buon punto\" → kept as text<br>• PT "
"(suffix = \"pronto\"): \"ponto pronto\" → \".\" — but \"um bom ponto\" → "
"kept as text<br>• UK (suffix = \"далі\"): \"крапка далі\" → \".\" — but "
"\"одна крапка\" → kept as text<br><br><b>Ambiguous commands that require the "
"suffix:</b><br>FR: point, deux points — EN: period, colon — DE: Punkt<br>ES: "
"punto, coma — IT: punto — PT: ponto — UK: крапка, кома<br><br><b>Non-"
"ambiguous commands (no suffix needed):</b><br>FR: virgule, point virgule, "
"point d'interrogation…<br>EN: comma, semicolon, question mark…<br>DE: Komma, "
"Semikolon, Doppelpunkt…<br>ES: punto y coma, dos puntos, interrogación…"
"<br><br><b>Per language:</b> Select a language in the combo box to set a "
"different suffix for each language.<br><br>In the rules editor below, "
"<code>%SUFFIX_XX%</code> placeholders are replaced by this value at runtime."
"<br><br>Leave empty to disable suffix-based commands for that language."
msgstr ""
"<b>Suffixe de commande</b><br><br>Certaines commandes vocales utilisent des "
"mots qui existent aussi comme mots normaux. Le suffixe est un mot que vous "
"dites <b>après</b> la commande ambiguë pour confirmer qu'il s'agit d'une "
"commande vocale et non d'un mot ordinaire."
"<br><br><b>Exemples par langue :</b><br>• FR (suffixe = \"suivi\") : \"point "
"suivi\" → \".\" — mais \"un bon point\" → conservé comme texte<br>• EN "
"(suffix = \"done\") : \"period done\" → \".\" — mais \"a long period\" → "
"conservé comme texte<br>• DE (Suffix = \"weiter\") : \"Punkt weiter\" → \"."
"\" — mais \"ein guter Punkt\" → conservé comme texte<br>• ES (sufijo = "
"\"listo\") : \"punto listo\" → \".\" — mais \"un buen punto\" → conservé "
"comme texte<br>• IT (suffisso = \"seguito\") : \"punto seguito\" → \".\" — "
"mais \"un buon punto\" → conservé comme texte<br>• PT (sufixo = \"pronto"
"\") : \"ponto pronto\" → \".\" — mais \"um bom ponto\" → conservé comme "
"texte<br>• UK (суфікс = \"далі\") : \"крапка далі\" → \".\" — mais \"одна "
"крапка\" → conservé comme texte<br><br><b>Commandes ambiguës nécessitant le "
"suffixe :</b><br>FR : point, deux points — EN : period, colon — DE : "
"Punkt<br>ES : punto, coma — IT : punto — PT : ponto — UK : крапка, "
"кома<br><br><b>Commandes non ambiguës (pas de suffixe nécessaire) :</b>"
"<br>FR : virgule, point virgule, point d'interrogation…<br>EN : comma, "
"semicolon, question mark…<br>DE : Komma, Semikolon, Doppelpunkt…<br>ES : "
"punto y coma, dos puntos, interrogación…<br><br><b>Par langue :</b> "
"Sélectionnez une langue dans la liste déroulante pour définir un suffixe "
"différent pour chaque langue.<br><br>Dans l'éditeur de règles ci-dessous, "
"les marqueurs <code>%SUFFIX_XX%</code> sont remplacés par cette valeur à "
"l'exécution.<br><br>Laissez vide pour désactiver les commandes à suffixe "
"pour cette langue."

